Should you use QUERY today?
For a public browser API, probably not as the only supported option yet. Too many parts of the delivery path may still make assumptions about familiar methods.
For an internal API where you control the client, server, gateway, and deployment environment, it is already realistic. Start by testing the complete path:

• browser or Node.js client;

• CORS configuration;

• reverse proxy and load balancer;

• API gateway or WAF;

• framework routing;

• logging and tracing;

• retry policies;

• cache behavior;

• test tooling.
The important distinction is between the standard and its adoption. RFC 10008 gives QUERY clear HTTP semantics today. It does not instantly upgrade every browser cache, CDN, router, and testing library.
